mio
------------------------------------------
An I/O abstraction layer replicating C file I/O API, supporting both file and
memory streams. It is meant to ease porting a program using C library file I/O
layer to allow in-memory operations.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.7-1
  libgcc1-4.3.4-3
  libglib2.0_0-2.24.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-9-1
  automake-4-10
  binutils-2.20.51-2
  cygport-0.10.0-1
  gawk-3.1.8-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-3
  libtool-2.4-1
  make-3.81-2

Canonical website:
  http://gitorious.org/mio

Canonical download:
  git://gitorious.org/mio/mio.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack mio-0.1.20100616git-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./mio-0.1.20100616git-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/mio-0.1.20100616git-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/mio-0.1.20100616git-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libmio0-0.1.20100616git-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libmio-devel-0.1.20100616git-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(mio)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/mio.README
  /usr/share/doc/mio/COPYING

(libmio0)
  /usr/bin/cygmio-0.dll

(libmio-devel)
  /usr/include/mio/mio.h
  /usr/lib/libmio.a
  /usr/lib/libmio.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libmio.la
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/mio.pc

------------------

